com.xatkit.core.recognition.dialogflow

Class DialogFlowEntityMapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.xatkit.core.recognition.EntityMapper
      • com.xatkit.core.recognition.dialogflow.DialogFlowEntityMapper

  • public class DialogFlowEntityMapper
extends EntityMapper
    An EntityMapper initialized with DialogFlow's system entities.

    This class provides a mapping of EntityTypes to DialogFlow's system entities. Mapped entities can be accessed by calling EntityMapper.getMappingFor(EntityDefinition).

      • addCustomEntityMapping

        public void addCustomEntityMapping(com.xatkit.intent.CustomEntityDefinition entityDefinition,
                                   String concreteEntity)
        This method is disabled for DialogFlowEntityMapper.

        DialogFlow entities are registered independently from the intents. This two-step process allows to reference entities with their names, and do not require to store any mapping information in the DialogFlowEntityMapper.

      • getMappingForCustomEntity

        protected String getMappingForCustomEntity(com.xatkit.intent.CustomEntityDefinition customEntityDefinition)
        Maps the provided customEntityDefinition to its DialogFlow implementation.

        DialogFlow entities are registered independently from the intents. This two-step process allows to reference entities with their names, and do not require to store any mapping information in the DialogFlowEntityMapper.
